# POS Frontend & Visualization Roadmap

## Goal Description
Build the user interface for the POS system to make the backend features accessible and usable.
1.  **Frontend Architecture**: Move templates/static to root and adopt component-based design.
2.  **Dashboard**: Visualize sales and profit data using Chart.js.
3.  **POS sale_panel**: A "Cash Register" screen for adding items to a cart and checking out.
4.  **Stock UI**: Interface for managing stock (restocking) with proper logging.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> **Technology Stack**: I will use **Vanilla JavaScript** (or simple Alpine.js if preferred) and **Bootstrap** (already in use) to keep the stack simple and consistent with the Django templates. No React/Vue complexities unless requested.
>
> **Restructuring**: Templates and Static files will be moved to the project root (`/templates`, `/static`) for better organization and reuse.

